 
Experiment 3: To study and implement basic HTML tags for creating a simple web page structure.
 
Introduction
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is used to design web pages. It uses tags to structure content like text, images, and links.
 
Basic HTML Structure
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My First Page</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello World</h1>
<p>This is my first web page.</p>
</body>
</html>
 
Basic HTML Tags with Syntax & Use Case
1. Heading Tags
Syntax:
<h1>Heading</h1>
Use: Defines headings (h1 to h6, largest to smallest)
 
2. Paragraph Tag
Syntax:
<p>This is a paragraph</p>
Use: Adds text content in paragraph form
 
3. Line Break Tag
Syntax:
<br>
Use: Breaks line without starting new paragraph
 
4. Anchor Tag (Link)
Syntax:
<a href="https://example.com">Visit Site</a>
Use: Creates hyperlinks
 
5. Image Tag
Syntax:
<imgsrc="image.jpg" alt="Image">
Use: Displays images on webpage
 
6. List Tags
Unordered List:
<ul>
<li>Item 1</li>
<li>Item 2</li>
</ul>
Ordered List:
<ol>
<li>Item 1</li>
<li>Item 2</li>
</ol>
Use: Displays lists (bulleted or numbered)
 
7. Table Tag
Syntax:
<table border="1">
<tr>
<th>Name</th>
<th>Age</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Bunny</td>
<td>20</td>
</tr>
</table>
Use: Creates tables
 
8. Form Tag
Syntax:
<form>
 Name: <input type="text"><br>
<input type="submit">
</form>
Use: Takes user input
 
9. Bold & Italic
<b>Bold Text</b>
<i>Italic Text</i>
Use: Text formatting
 
10. Div Tag
<div>
 Content here
</div>
Use: Groups elements for styling/layout
 
Conclusion
Basic HTML tags help in structuring web pages effectively. Understanding these tags is essential for web development.
